 Usage instructions

This workflow executes the given MySQL scripts on the target database. Prior to execution of the script, following checks are executed as prescribed by the user\:
             -	Check for Prohibited Database Commands
             -	Check for Prohibited Grant Privileges
             -	Check for User specified regular expression.
             -	 Syntax Check
The given scripts are executed one by one. When any one of the script fails, the workflow exits with failure status. If you specify the rollback script to be executed on failure, the given rollback scripts are executed.

 Dependencies

The database user needs to have necessary permission on the database on which the script is being executed.

 Results verification

None.

 Notification plan

None.
 Required Inputs

    Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
    Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
    Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
    Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
    Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
    Check MySQL Syntax Run Flag - *Required - Boolean parameter to specify whether syntax check needs to be executed on the MySQL Scripts and on the Rollback Scripts. Default Value is Y.
    Check Prohibited Grant Privileges Run Flag - *Required - Boolean parameter to specify whether the MySQL Script file needs to be checked for prohibited grant privilege commands. Default Value is Y.
    Check Prohibited MySQL Commands Run Flag - *Required - Boolean parameter to specify whether the MySQL Script file needs to be checked for prohibited MySQL commands. Default Value is Y.
    Check Prohibited Regular Expression Run Flag - *Required - Boolean parameter to specify whether the MySQL Script file needs to be checked for user specified regular expression. Default Value is Y.
    Database Password - *Required - Password to connect to the database.
    Database User Name - *Required - User Account to connect to the database.
    Database.Name - No description
    Display MySQL Script Output - *Required - Boolean parameter to specify whether the output of MySQL Script file is to be displayed on DMA console.
    Display SQL Length - *Required - Integer specifying the length of the MySQL script file to be displayed on DMA console in case of exception. Default Value is 200.
    Execute Rollback on Failure - *Required - Boolean parameter to specify whether rollback script is to be executed on failure of execution of MySQL script files. Default Value is N.
    Instance.Port - No description
    MySQL Script List - *Required - Comma separated list of script files to be executed on the target database.
    Staging Directory - *Required - Directory to place the Scripts downloaded from SA core. Default value is /tmp/mysql_sql_release.

 Optional Inputs

    Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
    Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
    Download From SA - Download binaries from SA (True || False). Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
    SA Folder Path - Location of binaries on SA. Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
    Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
    Prohibited MySQL Commands - *Optional - Comma separated list of prohibited MySQL commands. Default value is create database, drop database, create user, drop user.
    Prohibited Regular Expression - *Optional - Regular pattern that should not exist in the MySQL Script file
    Rollback Script List - *Optional - Comma separated list of rollback scripts to be executed on failure of execution of MySQL scripts.
    Prohibited Grant Privileges - *Optional - Comma separated list of prohibited grant privilege commands. Default value is grant all, grant insert, grant create user, grant delete, grant select , grant create routine, grant execute on.
